GameCell - Class in supportingClasses
This class is the basis for all game play.

Creates a new GameCell object using the given cell type, row, and column; This should be the main constructor used (especially when generating maps);
GameCell() - Constructor for class supportingClasses.GameCell
 
GameCellContainer - Class in supportingClasses
Provides a stable area where animations can be rendered on top of game cells; I created this class because adding animations to an individual GameCell was not practical because I would have had to change the entire structure of each GameCell so that it extended a pane which had a canvas embedded within it.
GameCellContainer(int, int, Node...) - Constructor for class supportingClasses.GameCellContainer
Constructs a GameCellContainer with the given row and column while passing the children to it's super class, Pane;
GameInfo - Class in dynamicStorage
This class holds all of the information needed to create or load a game and is constantly updated throughout game play.
GameInfo() - Constructor for class dynamicStorage.GameInfo
Creates a new GameInfo object in saveSlot 1 with the playerName "DEFAULT" and "EASY" difficulty; Generates a new random game map; Sets timeElapsed to 0; Sets score to 0; Sets resource values and resource max values to class constant values;
GameInfo(int, String, String) - Constructor for class dynamicStorage.GameInfo
Creates a new GameInfo object with the passed in saveSlot number, playerName, and difficulty; Generates a new random game map; Sets timeElapsed to 0; Sets score to 0; Sets resource values and resource max values to class constant values;
GameLogic - Class in main
Analyzes the current game map and performs calculations for running the game; TERMINOLOGY USED IN THIS CLASS 1) enemy spread - an event where the enemies in each hostile cell spread to one random cell that is one step away; each enemy spread is accompanied by objectives regenerating their enemies; occurs at different times depending on the difficulty of the current game; 2) step - see explanation below Throughout this class I will use a term called "steps".
GameLogic(GameInfo) - Constructor for class main.GameLogic
Creates a new GameLogic object with the passed GameInfo object
